io.spine.server

Class BoundedContext.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.server.BoundedContext.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    BoundedContext

    public static class BoundedContext.Builder
extends java.lang.Object
    A builder for producing BoundedContext instances.

    An application can have more than one bounded context. To distinguish them use BoundedContext.Builder.setName(String). If no ID is given the default ID will be assigned.

      • setName

        public BoundedContext.Builder setName(java.lang.String name)
        Sets the name for a new bounded context.

        If the name is not defined in the builder, the context will get BoundedContext.DEFAULT_NAME.

        It is the responsibility of an application developer to provide meaningful and unique names for bounded contexts. The framework does not check for duplication of names.

        Parameters:
        name - an identifier string for a new bounded context. Cannot be null, empty, or blank

      • getName
